Stay Safe Online – Prevention Checklist (For College Students in India)
Do not share OTP, UPI PIN, bank details, or passwords with anyone — even if they claim to be from the bank or customer care.

Always read UPI notifications carefully. Remember: approving a collect request sends money — it does not receive money.

Avoid clicking unknown links received through SMS, email, WhatsApp, Telegram, or social media. They may lead to phishing or malware.

Download apps only from trusted sources like the Google Play Store or Apple App Store. Do not install screen-sharing or remote access apps on strangers’ instructions.

Use strong, unique passwords for email, banking, and social media accounts. Enable two-factor authentication (2FA) wherever possible.

Avoid using public Wi-Fi for financial transactions or logging into important accounts. Use mobile data or a secure private network instead.

Keep your phone and apps updated to protect against security vulnerabilities and cyber threats. Install antivirus/security apps if possible.

Verify online buyers/sellers or job offers before making or accepting payments. If a deal sounds too good to be true, it probably is.
